The paper deals with data structures for external memory, which is a common topic in computer science and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The use of B-trees and the adaptation to online queries suggests a focus on databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses lower bounds and competitive analysis, which are common in algorithms research (cs.AL). The use of external memory and the optimization of I/O performance suggests a focus on distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses the transformation of BSTs into B-trees, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
